article.description: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 70, Monmouth, N.J. 52
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 70, Monmouth, N.J. 52
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 70, Monmouth, N.J. 52
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Shawn Atupem scored 16 points and grabbed seven rebounds as Mount St. Mary's of Maryland beat Monmouth of New Jersey 70-52 on Saturday night. It was the sixth consecutive win for the Mountaineers (11-9, 6-3 Northeast Conference). Jean Cajou added 13 points and five steals, while Kelly Beidler had 10 points, nine rebounds and six assists for the Mountaineers. Mount St. Mary's limited Monmouth (6-15, 4-5) to 35.2 percent shooting from the field, and forced 19 turnovers. Will Campbell was the only player to reach double-figures in scoring for Monmouth, finishing with 11 points. Travis Taylor added nine points and 10 rebounds for the Hawks, who came in having won five of eight following a 1-11 start.
